⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Ged (Sparrowhawk)
node U1 · U1 · ⟦Ged (Sparrowhawk):U1:523d5b⟧

WHO   — Ged (Sparrowhawk) — the Archmage · the wizard who named his own shadow
WHAT  — The central wizard of Earthsea — student of Roke, Archmage, and at the last the man who spent all his power to heal the breach between life and death.
WHERE — U1 · Le Guin  Framework inputs: Earthsea  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because power without balance is ruin; because to know the true name of a thing is to hold it, and to misuse that knowing is to break the Equilibrium of the world.
HOW   — By the lore of true names, by the silence learned from Ogion, by sailing to the ends of the sea and into the dry land of the dead — and by naming his shadow with his own name.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  To light a candle is to cast a shadow — and a wizard's first lesson is to learn his own.

